      "content": "Even small insects can certainly cause significant problems, although they usually don't completely plug the tube immediately. A small bug can partially obstruct the opening, which begins to distort the airflow dynamics and introduce measurable errors in the pressure readings. While a large blockage is catastrophic, even a slight partial obstruction can cause the instrument to read an airspeed that is either too high or too low, requiring the pilot to be extra vigilant for discrepancies.",
